As much as 13,600 liters (3,588
gallons) of diesel fuel spilled into the Danube river today in
the Slovak capital, Bratislava,  Sme  reported, citing an
unidentified official at the  Environment Ministry .  The fuel leaked into the river during the loading of a
tanker at the cityâ€™s port, the newspaper said. Crews are working
at the site of the accident to contain the spill, Sme said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
